20/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- With a 2-0 win on Friday (18 June), Denmark ended Bulgaria's European Championship hopes.
It was Bulgaria's second defeat after a 0-5 thrashing at the hands of Sweden.The Bulgarians will play Italy in their final game in Portugal.
Jon Dahl Tomasson scored the first goal at the end of the first half.
Jesper Gronkjaer hammered in the second one at the end of the game when Bulgaria was a man down, following a red card for team captain Stilian Petrov.
The Bulgarians also had a few opportunities.
Martin Petrov wasted the best one when he was left alone with the goalkeeper;
his shot was too weak to cause problems for the Danes.
(Bloomberg, AP, AFP, Reuters - 19/06/04)
